Cell["\<\
There are only 48 third-order left-dressed disjoint direct diagrams with \
non-identical one-body vertices. The multiplicity check is fulfilled.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9123230368435626`*^9, 3.9123230551958413`*^9}, {
   3.912323659514346*^9, 3.9123236716412516`*^9}, 3.9123313086853094`*^9, {
   3.912333581512753*^9, 3.9123335898394504`*^9}, {3.9137837486686153`*^9, 
   3.913783765160965*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6cbfffa1-aee9-476a-a443-\
22c18ea3cf3a"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Left-dressed disjoint direct diagrams with two identical one-body vertices\
\>", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9123225301750393`*^9, 3.9123225545237913`*^9}, {
  3.9123287170256085`*^9, 3.9123287269030876`*^9}, {3.912328804026425*^9, 
  3.9123288049892793`*^9}, {3.913783820070137*^9, 
  3.9137838212572823`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4c4a81d0-69a6-4f3d-a203-\
d77db1634d7d"],

Cell["\<\
Depending on the components of the one-body potential into play, symmetry \
rules may apply and reduce the total number of fully-contracted terms. When \
the multiplied Nambu components of the one-body potential are identical, \
vertex exchange is possible, hence the filtration process is necessary. \
Without loss of generality, let us assume that fully contracted terms which \
are mapped one another by the single-particle-index transposition e \
\[RightTeeArrow]g \[Wedge] f \[RightTeeArrow] h are equivalent, thus one of \
the two can be dropped, incrementing the associated multiplicity by unity. In \
the end of the process, 24 inequivalent fully-contracted terms corresponding \
to left-dressed disjoint direct diagrams are found.  \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8836806708732624`*^9, 3.883680671103075*^9}, {
   3.8836807100445924`*^9, 3.8836809748029747`*^9}, {3.88368106035993*^9, 
   3.88368123630155*^9}, {3.8884066008391533`*^9, 3.8884066027299986`*^9}, {
   3.889531897043619*^9, 3.889531903637968*^9}, {3.8895328025200243`*^9, 
   3.889532803452654*^9}, 3.9118851261633663`*^9, {3.911885313489254*^9, 
   3.9118853244102707`*^9}, {3.911885420747136*^9, 3.9118854315063624`*^9}, {
   3.9118860757937164`*^9, 3.911886076363371*^9}, {3.9118863981279774`*^9, 
   3.911886399679015*^9}, {3.9123232066276617`*^9, 3.9123232476938877`*^9}, {
   3.9123233347954187`*^9, 3.912323606712844*^9}, {3.912335104884133*^9, 
   3.91233512664951*^9}, 3.912335585399894*^9, {3.912336753830852*^9, 
   3.912336763901738*^9}, {3.912339194942795*^9, 3.9123392110274544`*^9}, {
   3.9123395015250535`*^9, 3.912339502808386*^9}, {3.9123396313792577`*^9, 
   3.912339631865156*^9}, {3.913783857041258*^9, 3.913783884990827*^9}, 
   3.9137993943066325`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"0f396342-4707-47d8-af2d-\
536866c4cad9"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"AdcdlVertex", "=", 
   RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
    RowBox[{"0", ",", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"i", ",", "1", ",", "48"}], "}"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"j", ",", "1", ",", "5"}], "}"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"k", ",", "1", ",", "2"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"MultdcdlVertex", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
    RowBox[{"0", ",", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"i", ",", "1", ",", "48"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Ifrepeat", "=", " ", "False"}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Temp", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
    RowBox[{"0", ",", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
