Cell["\<\
Depending on the components of the one-body potential into play, symmetry \
rules may apply and reduce the total number of fully-contracted terms. When \
the multiplied Nambu components of the one-body potential are identical, \
vertex exchange is possible, hence the filtration process is necessary. When \
the three one-body vertices are identical, the fully contracted terms which \
are mapped one another by the single-particle-index transpositions \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8836806708732624`*^9, 3.883680671103075*^9}, {
   3.8836807100445924`*^9, 3.8836809748029747`*^9}, {3.88368106035993*^9, 
   3.88368123630155*^9}, {3.8884066008391533`*^9, 3.8884066027299986`*^9}, {
   3.889531897043619*^9, 3.889531903637968*^9}, {3.8895328025200243`*^9, 
   3.889532803452654*^9}, 3.9118851261633663`*^9, {3.911885313489254*^9, 
   3.9118853244102707`*^9}, {3.911885420747136*^9, 3.9118854315063624`*^9}, {
   3.9118860757937164`*^9, 3.911886076363371*^9}, {3.9118863981279774`*^9, 
   3.911886399679015*^9}, {3.9123232066276617`*^9, 3.9123232476938877`*^9}, {
   3.9123233347954187`*^9, 3.912323606712844*^9}, {3.912335104884133*^9, 
   3.91233512664951*^9}, 3.912335585399894*^9, {3.912336753830852*^9, 
   3.912336763901738*^9}, {3.912339194942795*^9, 3.9123392110274544`*^9}, {
   3.9123395015250535`*^9, 3.912339502808386*^9}, {3.9123396313792577`*^9, 
   3.912339631865156*^9}, {3.913783857041258*^9, 3.913783884990827*^9}, {
   3.913785033160533*^9, 3.9137852374980774`*^9}, {3.9137852718199944`*^9, 
   3.9137853325774336`*^9}, {3.91378652405511*^9, 
   3.913786536077306*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1e1956ec-99c4-449c-b7f4-\
a29f9f4af0b8"],

Cell["\<\
e \[RightTeeArrow]g \[Wedge] f \[RightTeeArrow] h  \[Congruent] (eg)(fh)(i)(j),
e \[RightTeeArrow]i \[Wedge] f \[RightTeeArrow] j \[Congruent] (ei)(fj)(g)(h),
g \[RightTeeArrow]i \[Wedge] h \[RightTeeArrow] j \[Congruent] (gi)(hj)(e)(f),
e \[RightTeeArrow]g \[Wedge] f \[RightTeeArrow] h \[Wedge] g\[RightTeeArrow] \
i \[Wedge] h\[RightTeeArrow] j \[Wedge] i\[RightTeeArrow]e \[Wedge] j\
\[RightTeeArrow] f \[Congruent] (egi)(fhj),
e \[RightTeeArrow]i \[Wedge] f \[RightTeeArrow] j \[Wedge] g\[RightTeeArrow] \
e \[Wedge] h\[RightTeeArrow] f \[Wedge] i\[RightTeeArrow]g \[Wedge] j\
\[RightTeeArrow] h \[Congruent] (ige)(jhf),\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9137853296492443`*^9, 3.9137855932454247`*^9}, {
  3.9137986864292564`*^9, 3.913798687424214*^9}},
 TextAlignment->Center,ExpressionUUID->"0b08b8b0-c679-4ee2-8d97-7008e9be2948"],

Cell["\<\
are equivalent, thus one of the six can be dropped, incrementing the \
associated multiplicity by 5. In the end of the process, 16 inequivalent \
fully-contracted terms corresponding to diagonally-and-antidiagonally-dressed \
disjoint Bogoliubov diagrams are found.  \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.913785320942859*^9, {3.913785616366067*^9, 3.9137856374662666`*^9}, {
